  "summary": "Package exfiltrates data to attacker-controlled Telegram bot",
  "details": "The file 66o.js (lines 31 and 34) contains hardcoded calls to api.telegram.org/bot.../sendMessage with a fixed chat_id, a well-known exfiltration pattern used to relay stolen data to an attacker-controlled Telegram channel. Combined with the package's short, low-information name and lack of any legitimate documented purpose, this is consistent with an active data-theft payload targeting anyone who installs or loads the package. No benign use case was identified that would justify a hardcoded Telegram bot destination in a published npm module.",
